{"title_page": "World Federation of Hemophilia", "text_new": "{{third-party|date=August 2012}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| name   = World Federation of Hemophilia\n| logo   = Image:2010WHD Logo Eng.jpg\n| type   =\n| founded_date      = 1963\n| founder           = [[Frank Schnabel]]\n| location          = [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], [[Canada]] <!-- this parameter modifies \"Headquarters\" -->\n| origins           =\n| key_people        = President Alain Weill<ref name=\"wfh\">{{cite web | url=http://www.wfh.org/index.asp?lang=EN |title=World Federation of Hemophilia | accessdate=2012-08-16}}</ref>\n| area_served       = Worldwide\n| product           =\n| mission           = To improve and sustain care for people with inherited bleeding disorders around the world.<ref name=\"wfh\"/>\n| focus             =\n| method            = [[Therapy|Treatment]], [[Aid]], and [[Education]]\n| revenue           =\n| endowment         =\n| num_volunteers    =\n| num_employees     =\n| num_members       = 127 National Member Organizations<ref name=\"wfh\"/>\n| subsid            =\n| owner             =\n| Non-profit_slogan =\n| homepage          = http://www.wfh.org/\n| dissolved         =\n| footnotes         = }}\nThe '''World Federation of Hemophilia''' (WFH) is an international non-profit organization dedicated to improving the lives of people with [[hemophilia]] (also spelled haemophilia) and other genetic [[bleeding disorders]]. It educates hemophiliacs and lobbies for improved medical treatment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wfh.org/en/about/vision-and-mission|title=Vision and Mission - World Federation of Hemophilia|website=www.wfh.org|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> 75% of people in the world with bleeding disorders do not know it and do not receive care.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hemophilia.org/About-Us/Fast-Facts|title=Fast Facts|date=2014-03-04|website=National Hemophilia Foundation|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\nThe WFH was established by [[Frank Schnabel]] in 1963 and has its headquarters in [[Montreal]], [[Canada]]. It has member organizations in 113 countries and official recognition from the [[World Health Organization]]. The current President is Alain Weill.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wfh.org/en/about/history|title=History - World Federation of Hemophilia|website=www.wfh.org|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n==World Hemophilia Day==\nWorld Hemophilia Day is held annually on April 17 by the WFH. It is an [[awareness day]] for hemophilia and other bleeding disorders, which also serves to [[fundraising|raise funds]] and attract volunteers for the WFH. It was started in 1989; April 17 was chosen in honor of Frank Schnabel's birthday.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldhemophiliaday.org/|title=WHD 2020|website=www.worldhemophiliaday.org|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n\n===Themes by year===\n* 2018: \"Sharing Knowledge Makes Us Stronger\"\n*2017: \"Hear their voices\"\n*2016: \"Treatment for All, The Vision of All\"\n*2010: \"The Many Faces of Bleeding Disorders \u2013 United to Achieve Treatment for All\"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.wfh.org/whd/en/default.asp |title=World Hemophilia Day 2010 | publisher=World Federation of Hemophilia | accessdate=2010-04-17}}</ref>\n*2009: \"Together, We Care\"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.wfh.org/whd/en/WHD2009.asp |title=World Hemophilia Day 2009 | publisher=World Federation of Hemophilia | accessdate=2010-04-17}}</ref>\n*2008: \"Count Me In\"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.medindia.net/healthday/World-Hemophilia-Day-2008.asp |title=World Hemophilia Day - 2008 | accessdate=2010-04-17}}</ref>\n*2007: \"Improve Your Life!\"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.madcowramblings.com/2007/04/17/world-hemophilia-day/ |title=World Hemophilia Day | accessdate=2010-04-17}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.wfh.org/ World Federation of Hemophilia]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:World Federation Of Hemophilia}}\n[[Category:International medical and health organizations]]\n[[Category:Health charities in Canada]]\n", "text_old": "{{third-party|date=August 2012}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| name   = World Federation of Hemophilia\n| logo   = Image:2010WHD Logo Eng.jpg\n| type   =\n| founded_date      = 1963\n| founder           = [[Frank Schnabel]]\n| location          = [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], [[Canada]] <!-- this parameter modifies \"Headquarters\" -->\n| origins           =\n| key_people        = President Alain Weill<ref name=\"wfh\">{{cite web | url=http://www.wfh.org/index.asp?lang=EN |title=World Federation of Hemophilia | accessdate=2012-08-16}}</ref>\n| area_served       = Worldwide\n| product           =\n| mission           = To improve and sustain care for people with inherited bleeding disorders around the world.<ref name=\"wfh\"/>\n| focus             =\n| method            = [[Therapy|Treatment]], [[Aid]], and [[Education]]\n| revenue           =\n| endowment         =\n| num_volunteers    =\n| num_employees     =\n| num_members       = 127 National Member Organizations<ref name=\"wfh\"/>\n| subsid            =\n| owner             =\n| Non-profit_slogan =\n| homepage          = http://www.wfh.org/\n| dissolved         =\n| footnotes         = }}\n<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Jones|first=Peter|last2=Robillard|first2=Line|date=2003-11|title=The World Federation of Hemophilia: 40 years of improving haemophilia care worldwide|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/14750930|journal=Haemophilia: The Official Journal of the World Federation of Hemophilia|volume=9|issue=6|pages=663\u2013669|doi=10.1046/j.1351-8216.2003.00831.x|issn=1351-8216|pmid=14750930}}</ref>The '''World Federation of Hemophilia''' (WFH) is an international non-profit organization dedicated to improving the lives of people with [[hemophilia]] (also spelled haemophilia) and other genetic [[bleeding disorders]]. It educates hemophiliacs and lobbies for improved medical treatment. 75% of people in the world with bleeding disorders do not know it and do not receive care.\n\nThe WFH was established by [[Frank Schnabel]] in 1963 and has its headquarters in [[Montreal]], [[Canada]]. It has member organizations in 113 countries and official recognition from the [[World Health Organization]]. The current President is Alain Weill.<ref name=\"wfh\"/>\n\n==World Hemophilia Day==\nWorld Hemophilia Day is held annually on April 17 by the WFH. It is an [[awareness day]] for hemophilia and other bleeding disorders, which also serves to [[fundraising|raise funds]] and attract volunteers for the WFH. It was started in 1989; April 17 was chosen in honor of Frank Schnabel's birthday.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.marketwire.com/press-release/Media-Advisory-World-Hemophilia-Day-Tulip-Sale-Event-April-15-2010-1147989.htm |title=Media Advisory: World Hemophilia Day Tulip Sale Event, April 15, 2010 | accessdate=2010-04-17}}</ref>\n\n===Themes by year===\n* 2018: \"Sharing Knowledge Makes Us Stronger\"\n*2017: \"Hear their voices\"\n*2016: \"Treatment for All, The Vision of All\"\n*2010: \"The Many Faces of Bleeding Disorders \u2013 United to Achieve Treatment for All\"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.wfh.org/whd/en/default.asp |title=World Hemophilia Day 2010 | publisher=World Federation of Hemophilia | accessdate=2010-04-17}}</ref>\n*2009: \"Together, We Care\"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.wfh.org/whd/en/WHD2009.asp |title=World Hemophilia Day 2009 | publisher=World Federation of Hemophilia | accessdate=2010-04-17}}</ref>\n*2008: \"Count Me In\"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.medindia.net/healthday/World-Hemophilia-Day-2008.asp |title=World Hemophilia Day - 2008 | accessdate=2010-04-17}}</ref>\n*2007: \"Improve Your Life!\"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.madcowramblings.com/2007/04/17/world-hemophilia-day/ |title=World Hemophilia Day | accessdate=2010-04-17}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.wfh.org/ World Federation of Hemophilia]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:World Federation Of Hemophilia}}\n[[Category:International medical and health organizations]]\n[[Category:Health charities in Canada]]\n", "name_user": "Amarg9494", "label": "safe", "comment": "Updated citations", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Federation_of_Hemophilia"}
